26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_engine_disp_sorgf119.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:31 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "nv50.h"
30#include "outpdp.h"
31
32static inline u32
33gf119_sor_soff(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp)
34{
35 return (ffs(outp->base.info.or) - 1) * 0x800;
36}
37
38static inline u32
39gf119_sor_loff(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp)
40{
41 return gf119_sor_soff(outp) + !(outp->base.info.sorconf.link & 1) * 0x80;
42}
43
44static int
45gf119_sor_dp_pattern(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp, int pattern)
46{
47 struct nvkm_device *device = outp->base.disp->engine.subdev.device;
48 const u32 soff = gf119_sor_soff(outp);
49 nvkm_mask(device, 0x61c110 + soff, 0x0f0f0f0f, 0x01010101 * pattern);
50 return 0;
51}
52
53int
54gf119_sor_dp_lnk_ctl(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp, int nr, int bw, bool ef)
55{
56 struct nvkm_device *device = outp->base.disp->engine.subdev.device;
57 const u32 soff = gf119_sor_soff(outp);
58 const u32 loff = gf119_sor_loff(outp);
59 u32 dpctrl = 0x00000000;
60 u32 clksor = 0x00000000;
61
62 clksor |= bw << 18;
63 dpctrl |= ((1 << nr) - 1) << 16;
64 if (ef)
65 dpctrl |= 0x00004000;
66
67 nvkm_mask(device, 0x612300 + soff, 0x007c0000, clksor);
68 nvkm_mask(device, 0x61c10c + loff, 0x001f4000, dpctrl);
69 return 0;
70}
71
72static int
73gf119_sor_dp_drv_ctl(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp,
74 int ln, int vs, int pe, int pc)
75{
76 struct nvkm_device *device = outp->base.disp->engine.subdev.device;
77 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
78 const u32 shift = g94_sor_dp_lane_map(device, ln);
79 const u32 loff = gf119_sor_loff(outp);
80 u32 addr, data[4];
81 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
82 struct nvbios_dpout info;
83 struct nvbios_dpcfg ocfg;
84
85 addr = nvbios_dpout_match(bios, outp->base.info.hasht,
86 outp->base.info.hashm,
87 &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &info);
88 if (!addr)
89 return -ENODEV;
90
91 addr = nvbios_dpcfg_match(bios, addr, pc, vs, pe,
92 &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &ocfg);
93 if (!addr)
94 return -EINVAL;
95
96 data[0] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c118 + loff) & ~(0x000000ff << shift);
97 data[1] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c120 + loff) & ~(0x000000ff << shift);
98 data[2] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c130 + loff);
99 if ((data[2] & 0x0000ff00) < (ocfg.tx_pu << 8) || ln == 0)
100 data[2] = (data[2] & ~0x0000ff00) | (ocfg.tx_pu << 8);
101 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61c118 + loff, data[0] | (ocfg.dc << shift));
102 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61c120 + loff, data[1] | (ocfg.pe << shift));
103 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61c130 + loff, data[2]);
104 data[3] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c13c + loff) & ~(0x000000ff << shift);
105 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61c13c + loff, data[3] | (ocfg.pc << shift));
106 return 0;
107}
108
109static const struct nvkm_output_dp_func
110gf119_sor_dp_func = {
111 .pattern = gf119_sor_dp_pattern,
112 .lnk_pwr = g94_sor_dp_lnk_pwr,
113 .lnk_ctl = gf119_sor_dp_lnk_ctl,
114 .drv_ctl = gf119_sor_dp_drv_ctl,
115};
116
117int
118gf119_sor_dp_new(struct nvkm_disp *disp, int index,
119 struct dcb_output *dcbE, struct nvkm_output **poutp)
120{
121 return nvkm_output_dp_new_(&gf119_sor_dp_func, disp, index, dcbE, poutp);
122}
